Yes, you can specify that only integer values are generated in the Pareto distribution by rounding the generated numbers to the nearest integer. Here's an example in MATLAB:

alpha = 2;
k = 1;

num\_values = 100; % Number of values to generate
rng('default'); % For reproducibility

% Generate values from Pareto distribution
y = k.\*(1-rand(1,num\_values)).^(-1/alpha);

% Round the values to the nearest integer
y\_rounded = round(y);
